===Etymology===
{{rfscript|Gothic}}
From {{etyl|enm}}, alteration of earlier {{term|hendi||handy, skillful|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hendig|hendiġ|skillful|lang=ang}} (as in {{term|listhendig|listhendiġ|skilled in art|lang=ang}}), from {{proto|Germanic|handugaz|handy, skillful, nimble|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Germanic|title=|handuz|hand|lang=en}}, equivalent to {{suffix|hand|y}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|handich||skillful, apt|lang=gml}}, {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|handec|lang=gmh}}, {{term|hendec||manual, hand-held|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|hǫndugr||sc=Latinx|efficient|lang=non}}, {{etyl|got|-}} {{term|||tr=handugs|wise, clever|lang=got}}.

